<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7807&amp;p=78955#p78955"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[ines header required for real hardware?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7807&amp;p=78955#p78955"><![CDATA[
The iNES header exists because emulators can't tell what kind of cartridge a game uses based on the ROMs alone. The purpose of the iNES header is to give emulators information about the board inside the cartridge where the game comes from. If the game is in an actual cart, the board is there with the ROM, there is no need to describe it.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=95">tokumaru</a> — Tue May 31, 2011 4:35 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
